:rubric=1. Mind.
S{Gloomy.}


:rubric=2. Head.
S{Dull, frontal headache with constipation or piles; or from checked haemorrhoidal discharge.}


:rubric=6. Face.
S{Flushing with heat of face and lips numb; pricking as if with needles.}


:rubric=8. Mouth.
S{Whitish coating of tongue, with loss of appetite.} S{Tongue coated yellow along centre or base, with bitter taste.}


:rubric=11, 12. Stomach and Abdomen.
S{Nausea, with cramp-like pains in stomach; with cutting pains in hypogastrium; with constipation during pregnancy.} S{Vomiting with pains and heat in stomach.} S{Weight in epigastrium.} S{Sharp cutting in stomach every few minutes while sitting.} S{Heavy dragging ache in pelvis.} S{Colic with flatulence and nausea.}


:rubric=13. Stool and Anus.
S{Pure mucous stools, or mucous stools mixed with dark substances; before stool, severe pain in lower abdomen; during stool, tenesmus; after stool, little pain; vomiting.} S{Dysenteric stools.} S{Haemorrhoidal dysentery with tenesmus.} S{Obstinate constipation with haemorrhoids; stools very sluggish and hard, accompanied by pain and flatulence.} S{Hard, lumpy, knotty stools.} S{Light dry balls.} S{Bowels more apt to act in evening than in morning.} S{Bowels not moved for days, constant pressure in rectum with a heavy dragging ache in pelvis.} S{Piles with constipation, or even with diarrhoea, bleeding or blind and protruding.} S{Feeling of sticks, or gravel, or sand in rectum; evening and night; B[>] in morning.} S{Flowing piles, haemorrhage incessant though not profuse, with alternate constipation and diarrhoea.} S{Itching or burning in anus with swelling.}


:rubric=15. Male Sexual Organs.
S{Varicocele with extreme constipation.} S{Spermatorrhoea kept up by piles and constipation.}


:rubric=16. Female Sexual Organs.
S{Uterine diseases depending on diseases of rectum and bowels.} S{Dysmenorrhoea with haemorrhoids.} S{Pruritus vulvae with haemorrhoids; during pregnancy.} S{Diarrhoea after confinement.}


:rubric=17. Respiratory Organs.
S{Haemorrhage from lungs with short, hacking cough, dark, tough, coagula enveloped in viscid mucus; uneasiness in chest, but no pain; with rectal symptoms.} S{Pains in chest alternating with piles.}


:rubric=19. Heart.
S{Cardiac hyperaesthesia.} S{Periodical attacks of faintness and oppression, B[<] slightest motion.} S{Palpitation in pile subjects; piles return as heart is relieved.}


:rubric=21. Limbs.
S{Tearing pain in arms, hands, and legs; frontal headache.} S{Tearing in both knees, passing down inside of legs to feet while sitting; dull frontal headache.}


:rubric=24. Generalities.
S{Sensation as if face and limbs were enlarged, with warmth, numbness and pinching as from innumerable needles lower extremities seemed not to belong to him.}

  
